transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey Roger, yes, hey, but thank you for being so patient and so classy. So I did—

Speaker 2: Exactly what you wanted, and I actually was able to help you out and elevate—

Speaker 1: This. But so I did three things. The first thing I did is I put a stop to all any—

Speaker 2: And all monthly shipments. And the second thing is I put a stop to any and—

Speaker 1: All monthly refills. And the third thing I did is I put a stop to any and all—

Speaker 2: Monthly charges, and I was able to catch this last batch and reverse it and—

Speaker 1: Credit your account of the $63.95. Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, okay, and just correct me if I'm wrong because what I'm looking at is I—

Speaker 1: Don't think you got the right ones, but I don't think you were—they working, am I—

Speaker 2: Right? Am I right? They weren't working, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, oh, they were. I just have too many of them. I got like, okay, almost three full bottles now, so—

Speaker 2: Okay, cool, cool. So if they were working fine, I just thought maybe you were under the impression—

Speaker 1: That they were too strong or maybe you weren't strong enough, but no—

Speaker 2: Nothing, fine. Okay, so in any case, should you need a—

Speaker 1: Replacement of anything, as long as you call me, my extension is 0037, right?

Speaker 2: Bud, my name is KT Goodrich. I'll always take care of you. My fingerprints are on—

Speaker 1: This. And then in light of everything I did for you, bud, I set up a—

Speaker 2: Red button for you so you can get refills on your own. So when you go to—

Speaker 1: Scoreblue.com, right? And you log in with your Gmail, there's gonna be a category—

Speaker 2: Called your prescription. In that category, Roger, I put a red button with—

Speaker 1: White font that says quick refill. Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, so you can click that button—

Speaker 1: Anytime. The only caveat, bud, is you can't get more than one refill within a 30-day—

Speaker 2: Period, and then two refills a year. Like, you all you need is 20 pills a year—

Speaker 1: You're good to go. So you're good for now, and just click that button, you know—

Speaker 2: Whenever you need it or call me if you need something stronger. I'll always do a—

Speaker 1: Replacement and then go from there. All right, bud. All right, so you're able to—

Speaker 2: Stop all charges and you reversed that already?

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, and when you go to—

Speaker 2: Scoreblue.com?

Speaker 1: Yeah, you're very welcome. When you go to scoreblue.com and you log in—

Speaker 2: Go to the category called your receipts. You'll see there that, um, that, uh, there's—

Speaker 1: A negative $63.95 that was refunded, and I was actually gonna send you a—

Speaker 2: Replacement, but you said you're okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you say they work fine, so I—

Speaker 2: Canceled that. You'll see that too, so I was just trying to get ahead of it, right? So—

Speaker 1: But you're good to go, and let us know if you need more or click that—

Speaker 2: Button as long as you get 20 pills a year or every six months, and then you're—

Speaker 1: Good to go. All right, bud.

Speaker 2: All right, I appreciate it. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you bet.

Speaker 2: Adios, bud.

Speaker 1: Bye.
